
Snake 9

There was still the most important class - Room.
What do we need to describe it?
Room dimensions (width and height) - times.
The snake is two.
The mouse is three.

It is necessary:

a) create an int width and height variable in the Room class.
b) create a variable snake of the Snake type in the Room class.
c) create a variable mouse of type Mouse in the Room class.
d) create for them all getters and setters.
e) create a constructor. The constructor must take three parameters: width, height and ... snake!